# 📚 Book Library

[![Framework](https://shields.io)](https://microsoft.com)
[![Frontend](https://shields.io)](https://react.dev)
[![Cloud](https://shields.io)](https://amazon.com)

A comprehensive full-stack Book Library application designed to manage a personal book collection. Users can securely authenticate, browse, add, update, and delete book records while seamlessly uploading and hosting book cover images.

The architecture comprises a **React 19** frontend and an **ASP.NET Core 8 Web API** backend. User identity management is powered by **AWS Cognito**, and book cover assets are hosted securely via **Amazon S3**.

---

## ✨ Features

* **Secure Authentication:** Complete user registration, sign-in, and sign-out pipelines.
* **Token Management:** Implements access token refresh and secure server-side token revocation.
* **Full CRUD Operations:** View, search, browse, create, edit, and delete books in the repository.
* **S3 Media Storage:** Dedicated upload engine for book covers routed straight to Amazon S3.
* **Pre-signed Access:** Generates temporary, secure S3 pre-signed URLs to display private objects.
* **Protected Endpoints:** JWT Bearer authentication safeguards all core book API controllers.
* **Persistent Storage:** Relational book metadata mapping managed via Entity Framework Core.
* **API Documentation:** Built-in interactive API discovery interface via Swagger/OpenAPI.
* **Serverless Ready:** Configured out-of-the-box for serverless deployments on AWS Lambda.

---

## 🏗️ Architecture

```text
┌───────────────────────────────┐
│        React Frontend         │
│                               │
│  React + Vite + Tailwind CSS  │
│  React Router                 │
└───────────────┬───────────────┘
                │
                │ HTTP / REST API
                │ JWT Bearer Token
                ▼
┌───────────────────────────────┐
│      ASP.NET Core 8 API       │
│                               │
│  Books API                    │
│  Authentication API           │
│  JWT Authentication           │
│  Entity Framework Core        │
└───────┬───────────────┬───────┘
                │               │
                │               │
                ▼               ▼
┌───────────────┐  ┌────────────────┐
│  SQL Server   │  │  Amazon S3     │
│               │  │                │
│ Book Metadata │  │ Book Cover     │
│               │  │ Images         │
└───────────────┘  └────────────────┘
                        ▲
                        │
                        │ Authentication
                        │
                 ┌──────┴───────┐
                 │ AWS Cognito  │
                 │              │
                 │ User Pool    │
                 └──────────────┘
```

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

### Frontend
* **Core:** React 19, Vite
* **Routing:** React Router
* **Styling:** Tailwind CSS
* **Icons:** React Icons, Lucide React
* **Utilities:** JWT Decode

### Backend
* **Core:** .NET 8, ASP.NET Core Web API
* **ORM:** Entity Framework Core 8
* **Database:** SQL Server
* **Security:** JWT Bearer Authentication
* **Specification:** Swagger / OpenAPI

### AWS Infrastructure
* **AWS Cognito:** Handles registration, tokens, and revocation.
* **Amazon S3:** Scalable cloud object storage for cover art.
* **AWS Lambda:** Native serverless API hosting compatibility.

